headline: Why International Paper (IP) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of packaging and materials company International Paper (NYSE:IP) fell 3.5% in the afternoon session after Seaport Global Securities downgraded the stock to Neutral from Buy, citing valuation concerns.

headline: Smurfit Westrock stock falls after Mondi profit warning rattles sector
summary: Investing.com -- Smurfit Westrock (NYSE:SW) stock fell 4.5% and International Paper (NYSE:IP) dropped 3.8% on Monday after competitor Mondi warned of challenging conditions persisting through year-end, with quarterly earnings falling below expectations.
